IPHONE NET SALES AND UNIT SALES DECREASED DURING 2016 COMPARED TO 2015. THE COMPANY BELIEVES THE SALES DECLINE IS DUE PRIMARILY TO A LOWER RATE OF IPHONE UPGRADES DURING 2016 COMPARED TO 2015 AND CHALLENGING MACROECONOMIC CONDITIONS IN A NUMBER OF MAJOR MARKETS IN 2016. AVERAGE SELLING PRICES (“ASPS”) FOR IPHONE WERE LOWER YEAR-OVER-YEAR DURING 2016 DUE PRIMARILY TO A DIFFERENT MIX OF IPHONES, INCLUDING THE IPHONE SE INTRODUCED IN 2016, AND THE EFFECT OF WEAKNESS IN MOST FOREIGN CURRENCIES RELATIVE TO THE U.S. DOLLAR.

THE YEAR-OVER-YEAR GROWTH IN IPHONE NET SALES AND UNIT SALES DURING 2015 PRIMARILY RESULTED FROM STRONG DEMAND FOR IPHONE 6 AND 6 PLUS DURING 2015. OVERALL ASPS FOR IPHONE INCREASED DURING 2015 COMPARED TO 2014, DUE PRIMARILY TO THE INTRODUCTION OF IPHONE 6 AND 6 PLUS IN SEPTEMBER 2014, PARTIALLY OFFSET BY THE EFFECT OF WEAKNESS IN MOST FOREIGN CURRENCIES RELATIVE TO THE U.S. DOLLAR.

