CAPITAL RETURN PROGRAM

IN APRIL 2016, THE COMPANY’S BOARD OF DIRECTORS INCREASED THE SHARE REPURCHASE PROGRAM AUTHORIZATION FROM $140 BILLION TO $175 BILLION OF THE COMPANY’S COMMON STOCK, INCREASING THE EXPECTED TOTAL SIZE OF THE CAPITAL RETURN PROGRAM FROM $200 BILLION TO $250 BILLION. ADDITIONALLY IN APRIL 2016, THE COMPANY ANNOUNCED THAT THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS RAISED THE RATE OF THE COMPANY'S QUARTERLY CASH DIVIDEND BY 10% FROM $0.52 TO $0.57 PER SHARE, BEGINNING WITH THE DIVIDEND PAID DURING THE THIRD QUARTER OF 2016. THE COMPANY INTENDS TO INCREASE ITS DIVIDEND ON AN ANNUAL BASIS SUBJECT TO DECLARATION BY THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS.

